Forex volatility fears depresses Manila stocks . - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - May 19 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - * Dow Jones fall Friday adds to gloom - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Manila stocks fell again at the open on Monday due to fears of another roller - coaster ride in the foreign exchange markets in the region , traders said . The composite index dipped 32 . 55 points , or 1 . 26 percent , to a year - low of 2 , 543 . 58 . " This is follow - through selling from Friday ' s foreign currency scare . A lot of investors are still shivering , " said Joey Roxas , president at Eagle Equities . Brokers said the 138 - point drop of the Dow Jones Friday and uncertainties on whether the U . S . Fed will change its rates on Tuesday added to the market ' s gloom . Liza Joson , research director at Amsteel Securities , said the market will closely watch the Central Bank ' s move in the next few days after it increased its overnight borrowing rate by seven - percentage points to 20 percent on Friday . - - DOLLY AGLAY ( 63 2 ) 841 - 8936 , FAX 817 - 6267 
